alerts.alert: CSP: Failure to Define Directive with No Fallback
alerts.name: CSP: Failure to Define Directive with No Fallback
alerts.desc: The Content Security Policy fails to define one of the directives that has no fallback. Missing/excluding them is the same as allowing anything.

instances.evidence: default-src 'none'; script-src 'self'; connect-src 'self'; child-src 'self'; img-src 'self' data:; font-src 'self' data:; style-src 'self'
instances.otherinfo: The directive(s): frame-ancestors, form-action is/are among the directives that do not fallback to default-src.

instances.evidence: default-src 'none'; script-src 'self'; connect-src 'self'; child-src 'self'; img-src 'self' data:; font-src 'self' data:; style-src 'self'
instances.otherinfo: The directive(s): frame-ancestors, form-action is/are among the directives that do not fallback to default-src.

instances.evidence: default-src 'none'; script-src 'self'; connect-src 'self'; child-src 'self'; img-src 'self' data:; font-src 'self' data:; style-src 'self'

instances.evidence: default-src 'none'; script-src 'self'; connect-src 'self'; child-src 'self'; img-src 'self' data:; font-src 'self' data:; style-src 'self'
instances.otherinfo: The directive(s): frame-ancestors, form-action is/are among the directives that do not fallback to default-src.

alerts.solution: Ensure that your web server, application server, load balancer, etc. is properly configured to set the Content-Security-Policy header.
alerts.otherinfo: The directive(s): frame-ancestors, form-action is/are among the directives that do not fallback to default-src.

alerts.name: Authentication Request Identified
alerts.desc: The given request has been identified as an authentication request. The 'Other Info' field contains a set of key=value lines which identify any relevant fields. If the request is in a context which has an Authentication Method set to "Auto-Detect" then this rule will change the authentication to match the request identified.

alerts.alert: User Controllable HTML Element Attribute (Potential XSS)
alerts.name: User Controllable HTML Element Attribute (Potential XSS)
alerts.desc: This check looks at user-supplied input in query string parameters and POST data to identify where certain HTML attribute values might be controlled. This provides hot-spot detection for XSS (cross-site scripting) that will require further review by a security analyst to determine exploitability.
